<TITLE> Bangladesh, Switzerland to sign deal on double taxation avoidance </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 9 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh and Switzerland will sign an agreement on avoidance of double taxation Monday. The signing ceremony will be held at the National Board of Revenue at 10.30am, the Swiss embassy in Dhaka said in a statement Sunday. Switzerland has 26 investment projects in Bangladesh with a volume of $118 million, according to the embassy. Companies having invested in Bangladesh include Nestle, Novartis, Holcim and Syngenta. According to the Board of Investment, Bangladesh signed double-taxation avoidance agreements with about 30 countries, including the US and China. bdn
